From: Winland Android Project
Date: Sat Jun 6 2026
Subject: KGSL+Zink+Turnip WSI patches for Adreno 650 (termux-x11)

This patch enables Zink (GL-on-Vulkan) on Adreno 650 via KGSL kernel
driver instead of MSM DRM. It adds a custom KGSL WSI image allocator
(dma-heap + ION fallback), forces tu_wsi_can_present_on_device to
return true (bypasses fd mismatch between MSM DRM and KGSL), and
includes necessary termux-x11 compatibility fixes.

Changes:
- tu_wsi.cc: Add kgsl_get_info callback, tu_wsi_can_present_on_device=return true
- wsi_common.h: Add is_tu_kgsl flag and kgsl_get_info callback
- wsi_common_drm.c: Add dma_heap_alloc/ion_alloc, wsi_create_kgsl_image_mem
- wsi_common.c: Remove HAVE_LIBDRM guards on DRM image type cases
- wsi_common_wayland.c: KGSL modifier negotiation (DRM_FORMAT_MOD_LINEAR)
- wsi_common_x11.c: Skip DRI3 compat check for KGSL
- meson.build: Always compile wsi_common_drm.c (no libdrm gate)
- tu_shader.cc: pthread_mutex -> mtx_t (termux 0007)
- eglapi.c: Zink default driver when no MESA_LOADER_DRIVER_OVERRIDE (0017)
- platform_x11_dri3.c: Return true even if DRI3 open fails (0017)
- zink_screen.c: Disable general_layout for Turnip (0018)

Applies: patch -p1 -d /path/to/mesa-26.1.2 < this.patch
